A vintage 1970s-style illustration showing a vast maze constructed from filing cabinets, bookshelves, and old computer terminals, rendered in muted orange, brown, and teal tones. In the center of the labyrinth, a tiny solitary figure sits at a wooden desk with scattered papers, surrounded by towering walls of disconnected learning materials. Floating above the maze are translucent threads attempting to connect different sections but fraying and breaking apart midway. The perspective is slightly bird's-eye view, emphasizing the overwhelming scale of the maze versus the small human element. Grain texture overlay and slightly faded edges evoke educational filmstrips from decades past.
